getComment

public java.util.List getComment()
Gets the value of the Comment property. This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the Comment property. For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 
    getComment().add(newItem);
Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list String
